I see Node failing on MacOS, which looks related to this PR's changes:
```
client credentials
dyld: lazy symbol binding failed: Symbol not found: _TLS_method
  Referenced from: /jenkins/workspace/gRPC_pull_requests_macos/workspace_node_macos_dbg_native/src/node/extension_binary/grpc_node.node
  Expected in: flat namespace

dyld: Symbol not found: _TLS_method
  Referenced from: /jenkins/workspace/gRPC_pull_requests_macos/workspace_node_macos_dbg_native/src/node/extension_binary/grpc_node.node
  Expected in: flat namespace
```
I haven't looked at the details yet, since working remotely isn't easy, but my gut feeling is that we are using the wrong set of OpenSSL headers somehow. Maybe @murgatroid99 can have a stab at that.
Jenkins: test this please
